history.content:
Out of all the upper div CS classes this fall, the one with the least demand is CS 164 Programming languages and compilers (88/140 spots filled 0 waitlisted). I'm curious as to why this is, and would love to hear peer/faculty thoughts on the matter. Here are some questions to get the conversation going...

Do you feel its a waste of time to study programming languages and compilers? (if so why) 

I know the class has a notoriously large workload, has this deterred you from taking the course?

Has Professor Sen's reputation deterred you from taking the course? 

If you've taken the course, what are your thoughts on it? is it worth it?

Are you waiting for professor Hilfinger's variant of the course in Spring 2018?

Why do you feel there is such a small demand for this course?

etc.
